<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title>PixelAid</title>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Nova+Square|VT323" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="./stylesheets/style.css">
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="parallax">
      <div class="logo-container">
        <img src="./media/pixelaid-logo.svg" alt="">
      </div>

      <div class="sign-in">
        <form class="sign-in-form" action="/login" method="post">
          <input type="text" name="username" placeholder="username">
          <input type="password" name="password" placeholder="password">
          <input type="submit" class="signin-button" value="LOG IN">
        </form>
        <p id="signin-error">{{error}}</p>
      </div>
      <div class="home-buttons">
        <a href="/signup"><button type="button">SIGN UP</button></a>
        <a href="/canvas"><button type="button">GUEST</button></a>
        <!-- <a href="/questions"><button type="button">QUESTIONS</button></a> -->
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="info-container">
      <div class="slogan">
        <h2>Gamifying the way recognize and help one another</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="workplace-stats">
        <h2>Why is workplace recognition and collaboration so important?</h2>
        <div class="graph-stats">
          <img src="./media/bar-chart.svg" alt="">
          <div class="stats">
            <p>41% of companies that use peer-to-peer recognition have seen marked positive increases in customer satisfaction.</p>
            <p>Companies with strategic recognition reported a mean employee turnover rate that is 23.4% lower than retention at companies without any recognition program.</p>
            <p>Peer-to-peer is 35.7% more likely to have a positive impact on financial results than manager-only recognition.</p>
            <p>(SHRM/Globoforce Employee Recognition Survey, 2012)</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="gamification">
          <h2>Recognition, Reward, Competition</h2>
          <div class="game-shit">
            <div class="game-stats">
              <p id="imp-game-stats">Gamification works because it taps into each of these motivators to keep employees engaged.</p>
              <p>Our software uses Gamification of workplace recognition to:</p>
              <p>1. Give Team member incentive to help one anotherâ€“ by facilitating it, and breaking each task into bite-size chunks</p>
              <p>2. Give team member the ability to recognize one  another and collaborate on team project</p>
              <p>3. Give the user a trigger or cue to complete the action, cash in points by helping create a team Pixel Board</p>
            </div>
            <!-- <div class="rplace-image">
              <img src="https://i.redd.it/wc436nf7fdpy.png" alt="">
            </div> -->
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
